**[1848, 11-30] Ms.B.1.6.2.84**

Estlin, J.B. to Samuel May, Jr. ... Distinguishes American and English
ideas on voting. More discussion of the French political troubles.
{{u}BAA{/u}.}

“Thank you for offering me ‘Despotism in America.’ I have long possessed
it, & have of course read it.” BAA: Very fearful of events on the
Continent. Though he usually associates with friends of “freedom &
liberal Government,” he couldn’t help but hope for some restoration of
order.


